{"id":38317,"date":"2022-10-07T14:32:41","date_gmt":"2022-10-07T10:32:41","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38317"},"modified":"2022-10-07T14:35:05","modified_gmt":"2022-10-07T10:35:05","slug":"urwah-amputated","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/10\/07\/urwah-amputated\/","title":{"rendered":"Urwah on Patience: \u2018Urwah\u2019s leg is amputated, he praises Allah"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Zuhri reported: When \u2018Urwah ibn al-Zubayr, may Allah have mercy on him, was afflicted with gangrene in his leg, it was said, \u201cShall we not call a doctor for you?\u201d \u2018Urawh said, \u201cIf you wish.\u201d A doctor arrived and he said, \u201cDrink this substance. It will ease your mind.\u201d \u2018Urwah said, \u201cGo away with your drink. I do not think anyone could drink such a substance but to lose their mind until they no longer know their Lord.\u201d Al-Zuhri said, \u201cA saw was placed over his left leg and while we around him, we do not even hear him wince.\u201d When the leg had been amputated, it made \u2018Urwah say, \u201cO Lord, You have taken from me, yet You have still left more to remain. If You have put me to trial, You have still granted me health.\u201d Al-Zuhri said, \u201c\u2019Urwah still recited his portion of the Qur\u2019an that night.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Mara\u1e0d wa al-kaff\u0101r\u0101t li-Ibn Abi\u0304 al-Dunya\u0304 135<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u064f\u0651\u0647\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0639\u064f\u0631\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0632\u064f\u0651\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0644\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0639\u064e\u062a\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064f\u0643\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0629\u064f